      <scopecontent id="aspace_5e03b1710190f291db69ae15868d7253">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This small collection contains papers pertaining to Julius E. Kuhnert (fl. 1880-1940), a wood carver born in Germany who later moved to the United States. Included in the papers are drawings, photographs, and one template of designs for buildings in New York City, Rochester (N.Y.), New Haven (Ct.), and elsewhere. One of the photographs shows wood carvings in the Sterling Memorial Library at Yale University.</p>
         <p>Julius E. Kuhnert donated these items to Yale University in 1978.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_b1e83061b0d835b9fa4d4689d03c178e">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Julius Kuhnert was born around 1880 in Germany. He later moved to the United States and died in 1940. He was trained as a wood carver.</p>  
      </bioghist>
